assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Tokushu Tokai Paper Co., Ltd. manufactures, processes, and sells paper products in Japan. It offers special material products, such as fancy, high-grade printer, canvas, functional, security, and information-use papers, as well as papers for protection and preservation. The company also provides industrial material products comprising containerboards, kraft papers, and converting papers. In addition, it offers household products, including paper towels, paper for food material, paper wipers, gifts, toilet papers, and laminated products. Further, the company is involved in manufacturing and sale of paper pulps, special functional papers, protective papers, and other papers used in electronics industry; purchase and sale of paper stocks, etc.; transportation and work in rail yard services; collection, processing, transport, and sale/purchase of waste materials; production of whisky; and warehousing, leasing, transportation, and selling of liquor products. Additionally, it engages in the civil engineering, building, landscape gardening, forestry, sightseeing, and other businesses. Tokushu Tokai Paper Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 2007 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
